rComments: He is one of the most brilliant scholars of the philosophy or psychology of religion that a serious undergrad could hope to study under. He is a teacher that thoughtful students will appreciate: a true philosopher and scholar. The lectures are brilliant. You must pay attention, not skip. These are not easy courses but they are worth while.

rComments: Amazing prof. If a student is willing to do the work Discenso is willing to do all he can to help but he won't breastfeed you. You need to be an adult. He's not as interested in students meeting a standard as he is in students being engaged. Just showing that you learned SOMETHING is enough for him.

One of the most brilliant professors U of T has to offer. Provides a much more in-depth approach to studying texts than most undergraduate courses, and encourages you to really engage with the material on a much deeper level.  If you are interested in the material, he'll do all he can to help you out. Highly recommend taking one of his courses.
